relevant_findings.general: Laying in bed in mild distress, alert and oriented times three.
relevant_findings.HEENT: Pupil equal, round, reactive to light; extraocular movements intact; no facial droop; tongue is midline.
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs, rubs or gallops; normal S1 and S2.
relevant_findings.pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally; no respiratory distress.
relevant_findings.abdominal: Soft, non-distended, negative sign, right lower quadrant tenderness with some rebound tenderness, moderate guarding, no signs of diffuse peritonitis.
relevant_findings.extremities: Moving all extremities, no edema, normal muscle tone.
